# DSP rules

In addition to the audio-rt rules. DSP-specific:

## Numeric format

- All audio is `f32`, planar by channel where convenient, interleaved at
  engine-output boundary.
- Sample rate is always known and explicit; never hard-code `44100` or `48000`.
- Phase / position state is `f64` (sample-accurate over very long tracks);
  audio buffers stay `f32`.

## Denormals

- Hot inner loops that feed back (filters, delays, reverbs) must protect
  against denormal numbers. Common pattern: add a small DC offset (~1e-25)
  or clamp to zero below threshold. Document in the comment.
- On x86 we may set FTZ/DAZ at thread setup; on Apple Silicon ARM, denormals
  default to flush-to-zero. Verify per-platform.

## Numerical hygiene

- No `panic!` from arithmetic. Use `f32::clamp`, `f32::max`, `f32::min`.
- Comparisons with `==` on floats: only with `0.0` for "is silent" checks
  (allow `clippy::float_cmp` locally with a comment). Otherwise compare
  with `(a - b).abs() < eps`.
- Zero-init buffers. Random buffer state from `Vec::with_capacity` then
  `set_len` is undefined behavior — use `vec![0.0; n]` or `resize`.

## Performance

- Branch-free inner loops where it doesn't hurt clarity.
- Prefer SoA over AoS for hot data. Comment when you do.
- SIMD via `std::simd` (nightly) or hand-rolled — only after profiling shows
  it helps. No premature SIMD.
- `criterion` benchmarks live under `benches/`. Track regressions in CI.

## Filters

- Biquads: store coefficients as `[f32; 5]` (b0, b1, b2, a1, a2) with `a0` normalized.
- State per channel: 2 floats (Direct Form II Transposed). Document choice.
- Coefficient calculation off the audio thread; only state advance on RT.

## Resampling

- Use `rubato` for sinc resampling (off-RT) or simple linear interpolation
  for scratching paths (on-RT, must handle negative rates).
- Forward and backward playback share the same code path. There is no
  separate "scratch resampler"; rate is just a real number, sign included.

## Things to avoid

- `dyn DspBlock` — use enums or generics.
- `Vec::push` in any DSP function — pre-allocate.
- `to_string` / `format!` for debug output in render path.
